---
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
const faqs = [
  { q: 'What counts as punctuation in this tool?', a: 'All characters that are not letters, digits, spaces, hyphens, or apostrophes are removed by default. You can choose to preserve hyphens and apostrophes.' },
  { q: 'Will it remove commas, periods, and exclamation marks?', a: 'Yes — commas, periods, question marks, exclamation marks, semicolons, colons, brackets, and all other punctuation are removed.' },
  { q: 'What is the "Preserve Hyphens/Apostrophes" option?', a: "Hyphens (-) appear in hyphenated words, and apostrophes (') appear in contractions like don't and it's. Checking this option keeps them intact." },
  { q: 'What is the "Collapse Spaces" option?', a: 'When punctuation is removed, it can leave extra spaces. The Collapse Spaces option reduces multiple consecutive spaces to a single space.' },
];
---
<BlogLayout
  title="How to Remove Punctuation from Text Online Free"
  description="Remove all punctuation from text instantly. Options to preserve hyphens and apostrophes, and collapse extra spaces. Free online punctuation remover."
  canonical="/blog/how-to-remove-punctuation-from-text-online"
  date="2026-07-02"
  readTime="3 min read"
  category="Text Utilities"
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <p>Removing punctuation is useful for text preprocessing, NLP (natural language processing), data cleaning, and preparing text for word frequency analysis. This tool strips all punctuation marks in one click.</p>

  <h2>How to Remove Punctuation from Text</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Paste your text into the input box.</li>
    <li>Choose whether to preserve hyphens and apostrophes.</li>
    <li>Choose whether to collapse extra spaces left behind.</li>
    <li>Copy the clean output.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>When to Remove Punctuation</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Preparing text for machine learning or NLP pipelines</li>
    <li>Cleaning data before word frequency analysis</li>
    <li>Removing formatting from pasted content</li>
    <li>Normalising text for search indexing</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="my-8 p-5 bg-violet-950/40 border border-violet-800/50 rounded-2xl text-center">
    <p class="text-slate-300 mb-3">Remove punctuation from text in one click — free</p>
    <a href="/tools/remove-punctuation" class="inline-block bg-violet-600 hover:bg-violet-500 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-xl transition-colors">Open Remove Punctuation Tool →</a>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
